Classification with Python

In this notebook we try to practice all the classification algorithms that we have learned in this course.

We load a dataset using Pandas library, and apply the following algorithms, and find the best one for this specific dataset by accuracy evaluation methods.

Let's first load required libraries:

About dataset¶

This dataset is about past loans. The Loan_train.csv data set includes details of 346 customers whose loan are already paid off or defaulted. It includes following fields:

Field Description
Loan_status Whether a loan is paid off on in collection
Principal Basic principal loan amount at the
Terms Origination terms which can be weekly (7 days), biweekly, and monthly payoff schedule
Effective_date When the loan got originated and took effects
Due_date Since it’s one-time payoff schedule, each loan has one single due date
Age Age of applicant
Education Education of applicant
Gender The gender of applicant

Let's download the dataset

Classification¶

Now, it is your turn, use the training set to build an accurate model. Then use the test set to report the accuracy of the model You should use the following algorithm:

  • K Nearest Neighbor(KNN)
  • Decision Tree
  • Support Vector Machine
  • Logistic Regression

__ Notice:__

  • You can go above and change the pre-processing, feature selection, feature-extraction, and so on, to make a better model.
  • You should use either scikit-learn, Scipy or Numpy libraries for developing the classification algorithms.
  • You should include the code of the algorithm in the following cells.

K Nearest Neighbor(KNN)¶

Notice: You should find the best k to build the model with the best accuracy.\ warning: You should not use the loan_test.csv for finding the best k, however, you can split your train_loan.csv into train and test to find the best k.

In [20]:
from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split
from sklearn.neighbors import KNeighborsClassifier
from sklearn.model_selection import cross_val_score
from sklearn.model_selection import cross_val_predict
from sklearn import metrics
from sklearn.metrics import ConfusionMatrixDisplay
from sklearn.metrics import confusion_matrix
from sklearn.metrics import classification_report

from sklearn.metrics import jaccard_score
from sklearn.metrics import f1_score
from sklearn.metrics import log_loss


#Without cross validation
best_val = 0.0
top_results = []
top_data = []
top_f1 = []
for features in xComb:
#create test df
    x_temp = X[features]
    x_temp = preprocessing.StandardScaler().fit(x_temp).transform(x_temp)

    X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split( x_temp, y, test_size=0.2, random_state=4)
    Ks = 20
    mean_acc = np.zeros((Ks-1))
    std_acc = np.zeros((Ks-1))
    f1_scores = np.zeros((Ks-1))
    
    for n in range(1,Ks):

        #Train Model and Predict  
        neigh = KNeighborsClassifier(n_neighbors = n).fit(X_train,y_train)
        yhat=neigh.predict(X_test)
        mean_acc[n-1] = metrics.accuracy_score(y_test, yhat)
        std_acc[n-1]=np.std(yhat==y_test)/np.sqrt(yhat.shape[0])
        f1_scores[n-1] = f1_score(y_test, yhat, average=None)[0]
        
    results = "The best accuracy was with features " + ",".join(features) + ": " + str(mean_acc[f1_scores.argmax()]) + " with k=" + str(f1_scores.argmax()+1)  + "and F1 Collections " + str(f1_scores.max())
    print(".",end = '')
    if f1_scores.max() == best_val:
        top_results.append(results)
        top_data.append([mean_acc,std_acc])
    elif f1_scores.max() > best_val:
        best_val = f1_scores.max()
        top_results = [results]
        top_data = [[mean_acc,std_acc]]
        
print("\n")

for [mean_acc,std_acc] in top_data:
    plt.plot(range(1,Ks),mean_acc,'g')
    plt.fill_between(range(1,Ks),mean_acc - 1 * std_acc,mean_acc + 1 * std_acc, alpha=0.10)
    plt.fill_between(range(1,Ks),mean_acc - 3 * std_acc,mean_acc + 3 * std_acc, alpha=0.10,color="green")
    plt.legend(('Accuracy ', '+/- 1xstd','+/- 3xstd'))
    plt.ylabel('Accuracy ')
    plt.xlabel('Number of Neighbors (K)')
    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.show()

# with cross validation 
from sklearn.model_selection import cross_val_score

best_val_cv = 0.0
top_results_cv = []
top_data_cv = []
top_f1 = []
for features in xComb:

    Ks = 20
    mean_acc = np.zeros((Ks))
    std_acc = np.zeros((Ks))
    f1_scores = np.zeros((Ks))
    x_temp = X[features]
    x_temp = preprocessing.StandardScaler().fit(x_temp).transform(x_temp)

    for n in range(1,Ks+1):

        #Train Model and Predict  
        Kneigh = KNeighborsClassifier(n_neighbors = n)
        scores = cross_val_score(Kneigh, x_temp, y, cv=10, scoring='accuracy')
        y_pred = cross_val_predict(Kneigh, x_temp, y, cv=10)
        mean_acc[n-1] = scores.mean()
        std_acc[n-1] = scores.std()
        f1_scores[n-1] = f1_score(y, y_pred, average=None)[0]

    results = "The best accuracy was with features " + ",".join(features) + ": " + str(mean_acc[f1_scores.argmax()]) + " with k=" + str(f1_scores.argmax()+1)  + " and F1 Collections " + str(f1_scores.max())
    print(".",end = '')
    if f1_scores.max() == best_val_cv:
        top_results_cv.append(results)
        top_data.append([mean_acc,std_acc])
    elif f1_scores.max() > best_val_cv:
        best_val_cv = f1_scores.max()
        top_results_cv = [results]
        top_data_cv = [[mean_acc,std_acc]]

print("\n")
        

for [mean_acc,std_acc] in top_data_cv:
    plt.plot(range(1,Ks+1),mean_acc,'g')
    plt.fill_between(range(1,Ks+1),mean_acc - 1 * std_acc,mean_acc + 1 * std_acc, alpha=0.10)
    plt.fill_between(range(1,Ks+1),mean_acc - 3 * std_acc,mean_acc + 2 * std_acc, alpha=0.10,color="green")
    plt.legend(('Accuracy ', '+/- 1xstd','+/- 3xstd'))
    plt.ylabel('Accuracy ')
    plt.xlabel('Number of Neighbors (K)')
    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.show()
    
top_results_cv

results = []

def show_results(true, tested):
    conf_mat = confusion_matrix(true, tested)
    disp = ConfusionMatrixDisplay(conf_mat, display_labels=['COLLECTIONS','PAIDOFF'])
    disp.plot(cmap=plt.cm.Blues,values_format='g')
    plt.show()
    print("Accuracy: ", metrics.accuracy_score(true, tested))
    print("F1_score: ", f1_score(true, tested, average='weighted'))
    print("Jaccard Score:", jaccard_score(true, tested, average='weighted'))
    

# test KNN
print("\nKNN Evaluation")
kneigh = KNeighborsClassifier(n_neighbors = 2).fit(x_best_knn,y)
yhat_knn = kneigh.predict(test_x_best)
show_results(test_y, yhat_knn)
results.append(['KNN', jaccard_score(test_y, yhat_knn, average='weighted'), f1_score(test_y, yhat_knn, average='weighted')])

# decision tree
print("\nDecision Tree Evaluation")
loanTree = tree.DecisionTreeClassifier(criterion="entropy").fit(x_best_knn,y)
#loanTree.fit(x_best_knn,y)
yhat_dt = loanTree.predict(test_x_best)
show_results(test_y, yhat_dt)
results.append(['Decision Tree',jaccard_score(test_y, yhat_dt, average='weighted'), f1_score(test_y, yhat_dt, average='weighted')])

# SVM
print("\nSVM Evaluation")
loanSVM = svm.SVC(kernel='rbf').fit(x_best_knn,y)
#loanSVM.fit(x_best_knn,y)
yhat_svm = loanSVM.predict(test_x_best)
show_results(test_y, yhat_svm)
results.append(['SVM',jaccard_score(test_y, yhat_svm, average='weighted'), f1_score(test_y, yhat_svm, average='weighted')])

# logistic regression
print("\nLogistic Regression Evaluation")
loan_lr = LogisticRegression(C=0.01, solver='liblinear').fit(x_best_knn,y)
#loan_lr.fit(x_best_knn,y)
yhat_lr = loan_lr.predict(test_x_best)
show_results(test_y, yhat_lr)
test_y_log = [1 if x == 'PAIDOFF' else 0 for x in test_y]
yhat_lr_log = [1 if x == 'PAIDOFF' else 0 for x in yhat_lr]
print("Log Loss: ", log_loss(test_y_log, yhat_lr_log))
results.append(['Logistic Regression',jaccard_score(test_y, yhat_lr, average='weighted'), f1_score(test_y, yhat_lr, average='weighted'), log_loss(test_y_log, yhat_lr_log)])
